<br>
Ok, I was playing around in South Ro wating to go to hate, while attempting to summon an SG.  I had a level 50 warrior friend there also waiting, and we got bored.  I summoned a snake that gave itself a damage shield and bet him 20pp he couldn't beat it in a duel, no burnout or anything, just the pet.<br>
<br>
now, i've dueled him before and depending on pet, it'd usually win, but it'd be close.  The monster summoning II damage shield procing pet kiled him in roughly 40 seconds with 85% hp left.<br>
<br>
granted this is a duel situation, but it made me realize that the monster summonings have the HP/ac etc of a water pet (prolly why none of them proc water pet proc, cause then it'd BE a water pet) but the damage shield of a 49 fire elemental.  For those who don't know, that's a bad-a$$ pet...<br>
<br>
Reason 2: &quot;farming&quot;<br>
<br>
also, the dizzle's effect is nice for farming lower level dungeons.  It's easier to have the pet aggroing everything onto itself and goes nicely with scintilation. this way, you don't get hit as much and don't have to waste as much mana.  an MS pet with a DS can take on probably every mob in sol A at once. Throw all your stuff into the bank exept for a bag ful-o-malachite and cats eyes, summon 7 glowing backpacks (destroy all but one stack each of the food/drink/bandaids).  head into a dungeon that drops a lot of fine steel, get a dizzle's MS, DS it, send it in, loot, repeat.  the only thing that'll wiegh you down will be the copper and silver, and when you've got 67 pieces of fine steel, sell to a vendor and come back... (especially good for sol a)<br>
<br>
Reason 3: Something to do while making you mana go up faster than C2)<br>
<br>
Ok, sure, you could summon an earth pet and reclaim, but where's the fun in that?  I was hanging around in WL to go to PoG, came in there oom and was trying to see what monsters i could summon in that zone. by the time I was sure I had seen them all, i was FM, and i specialize in evocation, NOT conjuration...<br>
<br>
and i'm sure there's more, but this, to me, is enough <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
biggerin, 51 elementalist, force of valor, tunare<br>
